cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically on improving keypoint localization under occlusions. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of neural networks and optimization techniques, which are common in the fields of machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The use of feedback and top-down reasoning also suggests a connection to neuroscience and cognitive science, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of probabilistic models, which are commonly used in natural language processing and information retrieval, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
